    <text id="B0705T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo wishes to know a few details about an upcoming school report.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF &amp;
                        AL</abbr> 4th <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9th <abbr expan="Sub-District"
                            >Sub Dist</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> A McDonnell<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub Asst Comr</abbr><lb/>Winchester
                            <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-23"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 23/68</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr>: - </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to request to be informed if the school report to be submitted
                    by Circular 26. from Richmond <abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 21/68 - is to
                    include those schools taught under the auspices of local church societies as
                    well as <del hand="h1">by</del>
                    <abbr expan="American Missionary Association">A Miss Assn</abbr>. Also if the
                    form on back of said Circular is to be considered merely as a guide by which a
                    form of proper dimensions is to be made up - or is said report to be submitted
                    on back of the Circular?</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A. Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
